Betty Friedan, a pioneer of the feminist movement, passed away at 85 due to heart failure.
Her groundbreaking book, "The Feminine Mystique," challenged societal norms and sparked a revolution for women's rights.
Friedan's legacy lives on through the progress made for women and girls.
Despite criticism of her past, Friedan's impact on gender equality remains undeniable.
Her work continues to inspire activism and advocacy for women's empowerment.
Friedan's contributions to feminism will forever be remembered as she paved the way for future generations of women to strive for equality and liberation.
